{"componentChunkName":"component---src-components-learning-center-learning-center-template-tsx","path":"/learn/cash-management/what-is-direct-deposit/","result":{"pageContext":{"contentfulData":{"metaTitle":"Everything You Need To Know About Direct Deposits | Brex","metaDescription":"Direct deposits are a fast, convenient and safe alternative to checks. Find out how you can benefit from electronic direct deposit payments with Brex.","heroReference":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"4IyUWVZ3ZbIbPjknAsgq8V","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-21T23:03:20.493Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-21T23:03:20.493Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"articleCover"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"image":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"6tCfSRKCweWtYyA6Tbkoe2","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2019-10-02T16:14:29.755Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-02T16:14:29.755Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"title":"Group2","file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/lrdkz6qgi9tt/6tCfSRKCweWtYyA6Tbkoe2/90ec2f109bfeecf51956ed65be44d2c3/Group2.png","details":{"size":309809,"image":{"width":1208,"height":684}},"fileName":"Group2.png","contentType":"image/png"}}},"title":"What is a direct deposit?","subtitle":"Electronic direct deposits offer efficient ways of transferring cash across bank accounts.\n","ctaSubtitle":"Find out how they offer a fast, convenient and safe alternative to checks."}},"contentReference":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"1sqAdEs1d7jGIp8KQ8VoN7","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-21T23:06:21.663Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-21T23:06:21.663Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"bodyText"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"A direct deposit is an electronic payment made into a checking or savings account. Transfers are sent from one bank account to another through the [Automated Clearing House (ACH)](https://brex.com/learn/cash-management/what-is-automated-clearing-house/) network, which connects over 25,000 financial institutions in the country. It is a fast, convenient and safe alternative to check deposits. \n\nPayroll payments are an example of direct deposits. Employers can send funds to their employees’ bank accounts without delay or the risk of losing checks in the mail. Recipients also benefit from direct deposits, as the money is automatically added to their account balance with no action required. \n"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"4gpnAL2kUIU4S5m5oTfiBj","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-21T23:06:29.626Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-21T23:06:29.626Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionTitle"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"What are the benefits of direct deposits?"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"7E25ne03r7dpjKCTZNmzVg","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-21T23:06:45.824Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-21T23:06:45.824Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"bodyText"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"Direct deposits offer several advantages over other transfer methods. When you receive a direct deposit, the bank will automatically pay the funds into your account. The bank requires no action from the recipient, meaning you do not have to accept the payment or visit the bank in person.\n\nThey are also more cost-efficient than checks. The transfer is electronic, which saves on the cost of printing and postage. Direct deposits offer better security because there is no risk of a check getting lost, stolen, or altered. All parties will have an electronic record of the payment without the need to manually record payment details.\n\nRecipients don’t have to wait for their check to arrive by mail or for the funds to clear. They can receive payment faster and withdraw the money immediately. The sender will also see their checking account balance decrease automatically.\n"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"6h7CUERTLlQiCs6YBwDQ26","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-21T23:07:03.349Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-21T23:07:03.349Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionTitle"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"How long does a direct deposit take?"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"2h6ypBatt1o0O7lWJWV6PF","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-21T23:07:41.899Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-21T23:07:41.899Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"bodyText"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"Direct deposits are one of the [fastest ways to transfer money](https://brex.com/learn/cash-management/how-long-to-transfer-money/). The funds will typically be available the next business day. Payroll and government payments like Social Security benefits and tax refunds are typically available immediately.   \n\nPayments by check can take a lot longer due to postage time and the need for banks to clear the funds. Delays can also occur if the check gets lost or stolen. Unlike checks, direct deposits are not subject to a clearing wait period, so you can spend or withdraw the money straight away.\n"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"76rGJO4knJu2LmrPKTfA5X","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-21T23:08:05.044Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-21T23:08:05.044Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"sectionTitle"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"How to set up a direct deposit"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"35ujXdfsz4jrjswjHzuqvy","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-21T23:08:22.904Z","updatedAt":"2020-03-02T11:03:16.650Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":2,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"bodyText"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"text":"You will need to provide an organization with your bank details to receive direct deposits from them. This information includes your bank account number, routing number, bank name and address, as well as the names of all listed account holders and the type of account (checking or savings).\n\nThe organization may require you to fill in a paper or online form. You can find all the information you need on a personal check, by contacting your bank, or logging into your online banking account. In some cases, the organization may allow you to provide these details with a voided check.\n\nTo make payments by direct deposit, you will need a business bank account, bookkeeping software, or a payroll provider that allows you to send ACH payments. Request the above banking information from the recipient to set up the transfer. It is also a good idea to check with your accountant to ensure you understand any regulations and disclosures relating to direct deposits.\n\nFind out about [Cash Management with Brex Cash](https://brex.com/solution/cash-management/)."}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"4hFnFVSTF0ok3JjMIuv6CO","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-21T23:09:29.184Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-21T23:09:29.184Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"fourStepTile"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"articleLinks":[{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"3c9aBJGWNy7VzlnxbhYcSR","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-03T15:53:35.479Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-09T08:47:44.896Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":4,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"articleHeader"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"category":"cash-management","thumbnailImage":{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"2z62sYWbnYcnWmkyGWO3Yj","type":"Asset","createdAt":"2019-10-02T16:17:29.255Z","updatedAt":"2019-10-02T16:17:29.255Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":1,"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"title":"Thumbnail-online-invoicing","file":{"url":"//images.ctfassets.net/lrdkz6qgi9tt/2z62sYWbnYcnWmkyGWO3Yj/01ecf25f553322eb25b951b81e56ce8b/Thumbnail-online-invoicing.png","details":{"size":20535,"image":{"width":273,"height":273}},"fileName":"Thumbnail-online-invoicing.png","contentType":"image/png"}}},"urlPath":"paying-by-invoice-advantages","title":"What are the advantages of using online invoicing?"}},{"sys":{"space":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"Space","id":"lrdkz6qgi9tt"}},"id":"3oZY4SmZiJ04QGpiSxci2y","type":"Entry","createdAt":"2019-10-03T15:57:21.898Z","updatedAt":"2019-12-18T15:40:08.499Z","environment":{"sys":{"id":"master","type":"Link","linkType":"Environment"}},"revision":6,"contentType":{"sys":{"type":"Link","linkType":"ContentType","id":"articleHeader"}},"locale":"en-US"},"fields":{"category":"cash-management","thumbnailImage":{"sys":{"space":{"sy